    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered here is a pristine 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a masterclass in lightweight engineering and rotary performance. This example retains its original 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged powerplant, delivering linear boost and exceptional throttle response across the rev range. The chassis remains remarkably rigid, featuring an unmodified four-wheel double-wishbone suspension setup and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential for optimal power delivery. The exterior finish exhibits incredible depth and clarity, while the interior preserves the driver-centric cockpit ergonomics with no typical wear on the bolster surfaces or dash plastics. Mechanically sorted with a documented service history ensuring the apex seals, vacuum solenoids, and cooling system are in peak operating condition. This is a collector-grade specimen for the purist seeking an unadulterated JDM icon.",
